{"type":"message","id":"b62d60a6","parentId":"ed7aa77f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:25:57.875Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1d388309ae7c48a48a338935","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:f7e9ca4c-262c-476f-a252-a8dc71d756ac\",\n  \"runId\": \"d30be165-ce30-4176-87e6-2789e7351308\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:f7e9ca4c-262c-476f-a252-a8dc71d756ac","runId":"d30be165-ce30-4176-87e6-2789e7351308","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773159957635}}
{"type":"message","id":"90559af3","parentId":"b62d60a6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:26:07.671Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9f60f95bd6dc42f4b9bb2181","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw agent framework architecture context scope\",\n  \"provider\": \"perplexity\",\n  \"model\": \"perplexity/sonar-pro\",\n  \"tookMs\": 9866,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"perplexity\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7ac9765ac07d5634\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n**OpenClaw** is an open-source AI agent framework using a **hub-and-spoke architecture** centered on a **Gateway control plane** that routes messages from channels (e.g., WhatsApp, Telegram) to an **Agent Runtime** for execution, with **context scope** dynamically assembled per session from static prompts, skills, history, and memory.[1][2][3]\\n\\n### Core Architecture Layers\\nOpenClaw's design emphasizes reliability via serial execution (\\\"Lane Queue\\\"), modularity through file-based configuration, and composable context. Key components include:\\n\\n- **Channel Adapters**: Handle inbound parsing, authentication, access control, and outbound formatting for platforms like Discord or Slack.[1][3]\\n- **Gateway Control Plane**: WebSocket server for routing, session resolution, security (e.g., token auth, pairing), health monitoring, and cron jobs/webhooks.[1][3]\\n- **Agent Runtime**: Manages the execution loop—context assembly, model invocation (e.g., Claude, GPT), tool execution (in Docker sandboxes), and state persistence.[1][3]\\n- **Lane Queue**: Enforces session-isolated serial execution by default to avoid race conditions, with optional parallelism for low-risk tasks.[3]\\n- **Four-Layer Foundation** (Model, Memory, Tools, Orchestrator): Model as stochastic CPU; Orchestrator handles state/context budget; workspace files (e.g., AGENTS.md, SOUL.md) define behavior.[2]\\n\\n| Component | Role | Key Features |\\n|-----------|------|--------------|\\n| **Gateway** | Routing & Coordination | Access control, multi-agent dispatch, presence tracking[1][3] |\\n| **Agent Runtime** | AI Loop | Tool interception, streaming responses, persistence[1] |\\n| **Lane Queue** | Reliability | Serial-by-default, isolation per session[3] |\\n| **Canvas/A2UI** | UI Interaction | Agent-driven HTML workspace on separate server (port 18793)[1] |\\n\\n### Context Scope and Assembly\\nContext is **scoped per session/turn**, balancing token limits via dynamic composition:\\n\\n- **Static Elements**:\\n  - **AGENTS.md**: Core rules, constraints.[1]\\n  - **SOUL.md**: Personality/tone (optional).[1][2]\\n  - **TOOLS.md**: Usage conventions.[1][2]\\n  - **Skills** (skills/<skill>/SKILL.md): Task playbooks, filtered by agent role/trust.[1][2]\\n\\n- **Dynamic Elements**:\\n  - Session history (recent messages).[1][3]\\n  - Memory search (similar past convos).[1]\\n  - Base system prompt from runtime.[1]\\n\\nThe **System Prompt Builder** merges these with tools and history, streamed to models; updates persist post-loop.[1][3] This \\\"Workspace-First\\\" approach allows behavior tuning via files without code changes.[2]\\n\\n### End-to-End Flow\\n1. **Ingestion**: Channel → Gateway (access/routing).[1]\\n2. **Context Assembly**: History + skills + memory.[1][3]\\n3. **Model Invocation & Loop** (propose tool → execute → backfill).[1][3]\\n4. **Delivery**: Stream response; persist state.[1]\\n\\nSecurity blocks risky patterns (e.g., shell redirections, chaining).[3] For multi-agent, routing and session tools enable coordination.[1]\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7ac9765ac07d5634\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": []\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw agent framework architecture context scope","provider":"perplexity","model":"perplexity/sonar-pro","tookMs":9866,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"perplexity","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7ac9765ac07d5634\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n**OpenClaw** is an open-source AI agent framework using a **hub-and-spoke architecture** centered on a **Gateway control plane** that routes messages from channels (e.g., WhatsApp, Telegram) to an **Agent Runtime** for execution, with **context scope** dynamically assembled per session from static prompts, skills, history, and memory.[1][2][3]\n\n### Core Architecture Layers\nOpenClaw's design emphasizes reliability via serial execution (\"Lane Queue\"), modularity through file-based configuration, and composable context. Key components include:\n\n- **Channel Adapters**: Handle inbound parsing, authentication, access control, and outbound formatting for platforms like Discord or Slack.[1][3]\n- **Gateway Control Plane**: WebSocket server for routing, session resolution, security (e.g., token auth, pairing), health monitoring, and cron jobs/webhooks.[1][3]\n- **Agent Runtime**: Manages the execution loop—context assembly, model invocation (e.g., Claude, GPT), tool execution (in Docker sandboxes), and state persistence.[1][3]\n- **Lane Queue**: Enforces session-isolated serial execution by default to avoid race conditions, with optional parallelism for low-risk tasks.[3]\n- **Four-Layer Foundation** (Model, Memory, Tools, Orchestrator): Model as stochastic CPU; Orchestrator handles state/context budget; workspace files (e.g., AGENTS.md, SOUL.md) define behavior.[2]\n\n| Component | Role | Key Features |\n|-----------|------|--------------|\n| **Gateway** | Routing & Coordination | Access control, multi-agent dispatch, presence tracking[1][3] |\n| **Agent Runtime** | AI Loop | Tool interception, streaming responses, persistence[1] |\n| **Lane Queue** | Reliability | Serial-by-default, isolation per session[3] |\n| **Canvas/A2UI** | UI Interaction | Agent-driven HTML workspace on separate server (port 18793)[1] |\n\n### Context Scope and Assembly\nContext is **scoped per session/turn**, balancing token limits via dynamic composition:\n\n- **Static Elements**:\n  - **AGENTS.md**: Core rules, constraints.[1]\n  - **SOUL.md**: Personality/tone (optional).[1][2]\n  - **TOOLS.md**: Usage conventions.[1][2]\n  - **Skills** (skills/<skill>/SKILL.md): Task playbooks, filtered by agent role/trust.[1][2]\n\n- **Dynamic Elements**:\n  - Session history (recent messages).[1][3]\n  - Memory search (similar past convos).[1]\n  - Base system prompt from runtime.[1]\n\nThe **System Prompt Builder** merges these with tools and history, streamed to models; updates persist post-loop.[1][3] This \"Workspace-First\" approach allows behavior tuning via files without code changes.[2]\n\n### End-to-End Flow\n1. **Ingestion**: Channel → Gateway (access/routing).[1]\n2. **Context Assembly**: History + skills + memory.[1][3]\n3. **Model Invocation & Loop** (propose tool → execute → backfill).[1][3]\n4. **Delivery**: Stream response; persist state.[1]\n\nSecurity blocks risky patterns (e.g., shell redirections, chaining).[3] For multi-agent, routing and session tools enable coordination.[1]\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7ac9765ac07d5634\">>>","citations":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773159967507}}
