\":\\\"subagent-complete\\\",\\\"targetKind\\\":\\\"subagent\\\"},\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"success\\\",\\\"id\\\":1,\\\"endedAt\\\":1773160074964}],\\\"total\\\":5,\\\"filters\\\":{\\\"limit\\\":20,\\\"offset\\\":0}}\",\"cwd\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\10906\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"}},\"metadata\":{\"agentId\":\"main\"},\"id\":71},{\"runId\":\"04dccc2e-c7c8-4172-b924-3346343f6149\",\"sessionId\":\"2accf470-a410-405c-ad91-2d1cb497176d\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:main\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_0a80b540210b4fc983f45e2f\",\"timestamp\":1773160240687,\"startedAt\":1773160240305,\"durationMs\":382,\"params\":{\"command\":\"Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \\\"http://127.0.0.1:18789/plugins/contextscope/api/stats\\\" -UseBasicParsing | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Content\"},\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"stats\\\":{\\\"totalRequests\\\":69,\\\"todayRequests\\\":29,\\\"weekRequests\\\":69,\\\"averageTokens\\\":0,\\\"totalCost\\\":0,\\\"byProvider\\\":{\\\"bailian\\\":61,\\\"openrouter\\\":2,\\\"anthropic\\\":6},\\\"byModel\\\":{\\\"qwen3.5-plus\\\":61,\\\"anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet\\\":2,\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\":6},\\\"hourlyDistribution\\\":[29,0,6,2,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,18,0,0,0,0,1,3,0,0,0,0,0,10]},\\\"storage\\\":{\\\"totalRequests\\\":69,\\\"todayRequests\\\":29,\\\"weekRequests\\\":69,\\\"storageSize\\\":\\\"18.4 MB\\\",\\\"oldestRequest\\\":1773081035652,\\\"newestRequest\\\":1773160240634},\\\"config\\\":{\\\"theme\\\":\\\"dark\\\",\\\"autoRefresh\\\":true,\\\"refreshInterval\\\":5000}}\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":376,\"aggregated\":\"{\\\"stats\\\":{\\\"totalRequests\\\":69,\\\"todayRequests\\\":29,\\\"weekRequests\\\":69,\\\"averageTokens\\\":0,\\\"totalCost\\\":0,\\\"byProvider\\\":{\\\"bailian\\\":61,\\\"openrouter\\\":2,\\\"anthropic\\\":6},\\\"byModel\\\":{\\\"qwen3.5-plus\\\":61,\\\"anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet\\\":2,\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\":6},\\\"hourlyDistribution\\\":[29,0,6,2,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,18,0,0,0,0,1,3,0,0,0,0,0,10]},\\\"storage\\\":{\\\"totalRequests\\\":69,\\\"todayRequests\\\":29,\\\"weekRequests\\\":69,\\\"storageSize\\\":\\\"18.4 MB\\\",\\\"oldestRequest\\\":1773081035652,\\\"newestRequest\\\":1773160240634},\\\"config\\\":{\\\"theme\\\":\\\"dark\\\",\\\"autoRefresh\\\":true,\\\"refreshInterval\\\":5000}}\",\"cwd\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\10906\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"}},\"metadata\":{\"agentId\":\"main\"},\"id\":70},{\"runId\":\"97e40f43-6fab-4eec-a005-3365c659f444\",\"sessionId\":\"a83f887e-f946-4df5-a367-ea8e85d9d602\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:subagent:837950ff-abf3-430b-a50d-166d58677c1e\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_50cdfa3577ba4a32bb6497d6\",\"timestamp\":1773160098048,\"startedAt\":1773160088887,\"durationMs\":9161,\"params\":{\"query\":\"Node.js v22 new features 2024 2025 ??��??1??��\",\"count\":10,\"freshness\":\"year\"},\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"Node.js v22 new features 2024 2025 ??��??1??��\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"perplexity\\\",\\n  \\\"model\\\": \\\"perplexity/sonar-pro\\\",\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 9271,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"perplexity\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"content\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"2ff9bae672ec3964\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nNode.js v22, first released on April 24, 2024, and designated as LTS in 2026, introduces significant enhancements in V8 engine upgrades, testing tools, performance, security, and module support[1][2][5].\\\\n\\\\n### V8 12.4 Engine Upgrades (ES2024 Features)\\\\nNode.js v22 integrates **V8 12.4**, enabling native JavaScript features without transpilation:\\\\n- **Array.fromAsync()**: Converts async iterables (e.g., streams) to arrays cleanly: `await Array.fromAsync(stream)`[1].\\\\n- **Set operations**: Native methods like `union()`, `intersection()`, `difference()`, `symmetricDifference()`, `isSubsetOf()`, and `isSupersetOf()`[1].\\\\n- **Promise.withResolvers()**: Returns `{ promise, resolve, reject }` for deferred promises[1].\\\\n- **Object.groupBy()**: Groups arrays by key function, e.g., `Object.groupBy(items, item => item.type)`[1][2].\\\\nAdditional V8 benefits include faster JIT compilation, improved garbage collection, and reduced cold starts for serverless workloads[2].\\\\n\\\\n### Built-in Test Runner (Production-Ready)\\\\nThe test runner is now stable (no experimental flag), with built-in coverage and **snapshot testing**:\\\\n```\\\\nimport { test, describe } from 'node:test';\\\\ntest('snapshot', (t) => t.assert.snapshot(result));\\\\n```\\\\nRun with `node --test --experimental-test-coverage` for reports (e.g., 94.3% line coverage)[1].\\\\n\\\\n### Performance and Streams\\\\n- **8-15% throughput gains** on web servers vs. v20[1].\\\\n- Improved stream APIs: Better backpressure, `stream.compose()`, and error propagation[2].\\\\n\\\\n### Security and Permissions\\\\n- Enhanced TLS 1.3 and runtime permissions: `node --experimental-permission --allow-fs-read=./config app.js`[2].\\\\n- Security fixes for V8 vulnerabilities (e.g., CVE-2024-6779, CVE-2025-14766) and HTTP/2 crashes (CVE-2025-59465)[3].\\\\n\\\\n### Module and ESM Improvements\\\\n- Stabilized **top-level await** in ESM for cleaner bootstrapping[2].\\\\n- `require(ESM)` support and optimized resolution[1][2].\\\\n- **Hashbang (#!)** mode for executable .js scripts[2].\\\\n\\\\n### Built-in Clients and APIs\\\\n- **Native WebSocket client** (`node:ws` module) for real-time apps, reducing dependencies[2].\\\\n- **fs.glob()** for pattern matching in file system operations[2].\\\\n\\\\n### Native Add-ons and Tools\\\\n- Stable **N-API v10** for ABI-compatible C/C++ modules[2].\\\\n- Better heap snapshots, DevTools integration, and `--report-on-fatalerror` for debugging[2].\\\\n\\\\nFor 2025 updates, v22 includes ongoing security patches (e.g., CVE-2025 series), but no major new features beyond initial release are detailed in current sources[3]. Upgrade guides recommend testing for ESM shifts and permissions[1][2]. Native TypeScript support is experimental[4].\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"2ff9bae672ec3964\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n  \\\"citations\\\": []\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"query\":\"Node.js v22 new features 2024 2025 ??��??1??��\",\"provider\":\"perplexity\",\"model\":\"perplexity/sonar-pro\",\"tookMs\":9271,\"externalContent\":{\"untrusted\":true,\"source\":\"web_search\",\"provider\":\"perplexity\",\"wrapped\":true},\"content\":\"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2ff9bae672ec3964\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNode.js v22, first released on April 24, 2024, and designated as LTS in 2026, introduces significant enhancements in V8 engine upgrades, testing tools, performance, security, and module support[1][2][5].\\n\\n### V8 12.4 Engine Upgrades (ES2024 Features)\\nNode.js v22 integrates **V8 12.4**, enabling native JavaScript features without transpilation:\\n- **Array.fromAsync()**: Converts async iterables (e.g., streams) to arrays cleanly: `await Array.fromAsync(stream)`[1].\\n- **Set operations**: Native methods like `union()`, `intersection()`, `difference()`, `symmetricDifference()`, `isSubsetOf()`, and `isSupersetOf()`[1].\\n- **Promise.withResolvers()**: Returns `{ promise, resolve, reject }` for deferred promises[1].\\n- **Object.groupBy()**: Groups arrays by key function, e.g., `Object.groupBy(items, item => item.type)`[1][2].\\nAdditional V8 benefits include faster JIT compilation, improved garbage collection, and reduced cold starts for serverless workloads[2].\\n\\n### Built-in Test Runner (Production-Ready)\\nThe test runner is now stable (no experimental flag), with built-in coverage and **snapshot testing**:\\n```\\nimport { test, describe } from 'node:test';\\ntest('snapshot', (t) => t.assert.snapshot(result));\\n```\\nRun with `node --test --experimental-test-coverage` for reports (e.g., 94.3% line coverage)[1].\\n\\n### Performance and Streams\\n- **8-15% throughput gains** on web servers vs. v20[1].\\n- Improved stream APIs: Better backpressure, `stream.compose()`, and error propagation[2].\\n\\n### Security and Permissions\\n- Enhanced TLS 1.3 and runtime permissions: `node --experimental-permission --allow-fs-read=./config app.js`[2].\\n- Security fixes for V8 vulnerabilities (e.g., CVE-2024-6779, CVE-2025-14766) and HTTP/2 crashes (CVE-2025-59465)[3].\\n\\n### Module and ESM Improvements\\n- Stabilized **top-level await** in ESM for cleaner bootstrapping[2].\\n- `require(ESM)` support and optimized resolution[1][2].\\n- **Hashbang (#!)** mode for executable .js scripts[2].\\n\\n### Built-in Clients and APIs\\n- **Native WebSocket client** (`node:ws` module) for real-time apps, reducing dependencies[2].\\n- **fs.glob()** for pattern matching in file system operations[2].\\n\\n### Native Add-ons and Tools\\n- Stable **N-API v10** for ABI-compatible C/C++ modules[2].\\n- Better heap snapshots, DevTools integration, and `--report-on-fatalerror` for debugging[2].\\n\\nFor 2025 updates, v22 includes ongoing security patches (e.g., CVE-2025 series), but no major new features beyond initial release are detailed in current sources[3]. Upgrade guides recommend testing for ESM shifts and permissions[1][2]. Native TypeScript support is experimental[4].\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2ff9bae672ec3964\\\">>>\",\"citations\":[]}},\"metadata\":{\"agentId\":\"main\"},\"id\":69},{\"runId\":\"97e40f43-6fab-4eec-a005-3365c659f444\",\"sessionId\":\"a83f887e-f946-4df5-a367-ea8e85d9d602\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:subagent:837950ff-abf3-430b-a50d-166d58677c1e\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_fefaab53f0414fd095748fee\",\"timestamp\":1773160088779,\"startedAt\":1773160081090,\"durationMs\":7689,\"params\":{\"query\":\"OpenClaw GitHub project stars latest release 2025 2026\",\"count\":10,\"freshness\":\"year\"},\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"OpenClaw GitHub project stars latest release 2025 2026\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"perplexity\\\",\\n  \\\"model\\\": \\\"perplexity/sonar-pro\\\",\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 7800,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"perplexity\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"content\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"07fb22d305c876eb\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\n**OpenClaw is the most-starred non-aggregator software project on GitHub, with over 250,000 stars as of early 2026, having surpassed React (243K stars) and Linux (220K stars) in under four months.** [1][2][5]\\\\n\\\\nLaunched in November 2025 by Austrian developer Peter Steinberger as a fully open-source, locally-run AI agent framework, it connects large language models to tools like WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and iMessage for tasks such as executing terminal commands, file operations, email handling, and schedule management.[1][3]\\\\n\\\\nIt rapidly gained traction: a 1-hour prototype evolved into the fastest-growing GitHub repository, reaching 175,000+ stars by early 2026 and topping historical lists by overtaking long-standing projects like React (13 years to 240K stars).[1][2][3]\\\\n\\\\nNo specific latest release details for 2025 or 2026 are available in the results; the GitHub organization (github.com/openclaw) lists 22 repositories but lacks version info here.[4] A January 2026 security incident (\\\\\\\"ClawHavoc\\\\\\\") involved malware via disguised skill packages, prompting restrictions by some tech firms.[1]\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"07fb22d305c876eb\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n  \\\"citations\\\": []\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"query\":\"OpenClaw GitHub project stars latest release 2025 2026\",\"provider\":\"perplexity\",\"model\":\"perplexity/sonar-pro\",\"tookMs\":7800,\"externalContent\":{\"untrusted\":true,\"source\":\"web_search\",\"provider\":\"perplexity\",\"wrapped\":true},\"content\":\"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07fb22d305c876eb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n**OpenClaw is the most-starred non-aggregator software project on GitHub, with over 250,000 stars as of early 2026, having surpassed React (243K stars) and Linux (220K stars) in under four months.** [1][2][5]\\n\\nLaunched in November 2025 by Austrian developer Peter Steinberger as a fully open-source, locally-run AI agent framework, it connects large language models to tools like WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and iMessage for tasks such as executing terminal commands, file operations, email handling, and schedule management.[1][3]\\n\\nIt rapidly gained traction: a 1-hour prototype evolved into the fastest-growing GitHub repository, reaching 175,000+ stars by early 2026 and topping historical lists by overtaking long-standing projects like React (13 years to 240K stars).[1][2][3]\\n\\nNo specific latest release details for 2025 or 2026 are available in the results; the GitHub organization (github.com/openclaw) lists 22 repositories but lacks version info here.[4] A January 2026 security incident (\\\"ClawHavoc\\\") involved malware via disguised skill packages, prompting restrictions by some tech firms.[1]\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07fb22d305c876eb\\\">>>\",\"citations\":[]}},\"metadata\":{\"agentId\":\"main\"},\"id\":68}],\"total\":10,\"filters\":{\"limit\":10,\"offset\":0}}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\10906\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773160406155}}
{"type":"message","id":"00f4be9f","parentId":"5b5dbb44","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:35:09.694Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户要求获取最新数据并写入文档，我已经获取了 stats 和 links 数据，现在需要更新 API 文档。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"已获取最新实时数据！现在更新文档：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01c39519f2764d37aba5ef3a","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"D:\\code\\request-analyzer\\API_DOC.zh-CN.md","content":"# ContextScope HTTP API 接口文档\n\nBase URL（默认）：`http://127.0.0.1:18789`\n\n插件路径前缀：\n- Dashboard：`/plugins/contextscope`\n- API：`/plugins/contextscope/api/*`\n\n示例数据（本机联调，实时数据）：\n- `runId`: `d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450` (主会话)\n- `sessionId`: `2accf470-a410-405c-ad91-2d1cb497176d`\n\n## 1) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/stats\n\n返回总体统计、存储统计与前端展示配置。\n\nQuery 参数：无\n\n响应（**最新实时数据 - Wed 2026-03-11 00:30 GMT+8**）：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"totalRequests\": 71,\n    \"todayRequests\": 31,\n    \"weekRequests\": 71,\n    \"averageTokens\": 0,\n    \"totalCost\": 0,\n    \"byProvider\": {\n      \"bailian\": 63,\n      \"openrouter\": 2,\n      \"anthropic\": 6\n    },\n    \"byModel\": {\n      \"qwen3.5-plus\": 63,\n      \"anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet\": 2,\n      \"claude-opus-4-6\": 6\n    },\n    \"hourlyDistribution\": [31, 0, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10]\n  },\n  \"storage\": {\n    \"totalRequests\": 71,\n    \"todayRequests\": 31,\n    \"weekRequests\": 71,\n    \"storageSize\": \"19.9 MB\",\n    \"oldestRequest\": 1773081035652,\n    \"newestRequest\": 1773160401776\n  },\n  \"config\": {\n    \"theme\": \"dark\",\n    \"autoRefresh\": true,\n    \"refreshInterval\": 5000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 2) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/requests\n\n按过滤条件返回 LLM 请求/响应事件列表。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `sessionId`（可选）\n- `runId`（可选）\n- `provider`（可选）\n- `model`（可选）\n- `startTime`（可选，毫秒时间戳）\n- `endTime`（可选，毫秒时间戳）\n- `limit`（可选，默认 100）\n- `offset`（可选，默认 0）\n\n响应结构：\n- `requests`: `RequestData[]`\n- `total`: 当前返回条数\n- `filters`: 实际生效的过滤条件\n\n## 3) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/analysis\n\n按 `runId` 返回聚合分析结果（token breakdown、timeline、insights 等）。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `runId`（必填）\n\n错误：\n- `400`: 缺少 `runId`\n- `404`: 找不到对应 `runId`\n\n## 4) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/session\n\n按 `sessionId` 返回会话级统计与分析。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `sessionId`（必填）\n\n## 5) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/links\n\n返回主/子任务（subagent）关联边列表（spawn/send/ended）。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `parentRunId`（可选）\n- `childRunId`（可选）\n- `parentSessionId`（可选）\n- `limit`（可选，默认 100）\n- `offset`（可选，默认 0）\n\n响应（**最新实时数据 - 5 个子 agent 测试**）：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"links\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"spawn\",\n      \"parentRunId\": \"d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450\",\n      \"childRunId\": \"97e40f43-6fab-4eec-a005-3365c659f444\",\n      \"parentSessionId\": \"2accf470-a410-405c-ad91-2d1cb497176d\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:837950ff-abf3-430b-a50d-166d58677c1e\",\n      \"runtime\": \"subagent\",\n      \"mode\": \"run\",\n      \"toolCallId\": \"call_60f8699638014350934e1bee\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1773160060751,\n      \"metadata\": { \"agentId\": \"main\" },\n      \"id\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"spawn\",\n      \"parentRunId\": \"d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450\",\n      \"childRunId\": \"17bd3df0-c3d6-4c13-a24c-12f2831684aa\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:9c036b78-14b0-4038-a2b3-9920b6fbd2e8\",\n      \"runtime\": \"subagent\",\n      \"mode\": \"run\",\n      \"outcome\": \"success\",\n      \"endedAt\": 1773160079402,\n      \"id\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"spawn\",\n      \"parentRunId\": \"d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450\",\n      \"childRunId\": \"d30be165-ce30-4176-87e6-2789e7351308\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:f7e9ca4c-262c-476f-a252-a8dc71d756ac\",\n      \"runtime\": \"subagent\",\n      \"mode\": \"run\",\n      \"outcome\": \"success\",\n      \"endedAt\": 1773160098284,\n      \"id\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"spawn\",\n      \"parentRunId\": \"d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450\",\n      \"childRunId\": \"d9fb5801-eb4b-40f9-83b4-290330b572a8\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:fbae7b89-32ee-41d9-a888-8a7ab241fbc1\",\n      \"outcome\": \"success\",\n      \"endedAt\": 1773160033750,\n      \"id\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"spawn\",\n      \"parentRunId\": \"d43888a1-d47d-4402-97fe-ad582d8b1450\",\n      \"childRunId\": \"03ac5510-4382-4c21-adbc-990bd26288eb\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:629cb399-5cce-43a5-a58a-55cfe9d4b9cd\",\n      \"outcome\": \"success\",\n      \"endedAt\": 1773160074964,\n      \"id\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 5,\n  \"filters\": { \"limit\": 20, \"offset\": 0 }\n}\n```\n\n## 6) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/tool-calls\n\n返回工具调用 span 列表（来自 `after_tool_call` 采集）。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `runId`（可选）\n- `sessionId`（可选）\n- `toolName`（可选）\n- `startTime`（可选）\n- `endTime`（可选）\n- `limit`（可选，默认 100）\n- `offset`（可选，默认 0）\n\n## 7) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/export\n\n导出请求事件数据。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `format`（可选，`json` | `csv`，默认 `json`）\n- `startTime`（可选）\n- `endTime`（可选）\n- `provider`（可选）\n- `model`（可选）\n\n响应：\n- `format=json`: `application/json`，内容为 `RequestData[]`\n- `format=csv`: `text/csv`\n\n## 8) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/timeline/detail\n\n返回某个 timeline point 的上下文快照。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `runId`（必填）\n- `timestamp`（必填，毫秒时间戳）\n\n## 9) GET /plugins/contextscope/api/timeline/compare\n\n对比两个 timeline point 的差异。\n\nQuery 参数：\n- `runId`（必填）\n- `timestamp1`（必填）\n- `timestamp2`（必填）\n\n---\n\n## 📊 多 Agent 测试总结（最新数据）\n\n**测试场景**: 同时启动 5 个子 agent 执行不同任务\n\n| Agent | 任务 | Run ID | 状态 |\n|-------|------|--------|------|\n| tech-researcher | 技术栈调研 | `97e40f43-6fab-4eec-a005-3365c659f444` | ✅ 成功 |\n| config-analyzer | 配置分析 | `17bd3df0-c3d6-4c13-a24c-12f2831684aa` | ✅ 成功 |\n| health-check-1 | 系统诊断 | `d30be165-ce30-4176-87e6-2789e7351308` | ✅ 成功 |\n| research-agent-1 | 网络搜索研究 | `d9fb5801-eb4b-40f9-83b4-290330b572a8` | ✅ 成功 |\n| code-analyzer-1 | 代码分析 | `03ac5510-4382-4c21-adbc-990bd26288eb` | ✅ 成功 |\n\n**测试结果**:\n- 总请求数：71 次（测试前 45 次 → 测试后 71 次）\n- 今日请求：31 次\n- 存储大小：19.9 MB\n- 子 agent 关联：5 条 spawn 记录，全部成功完成\n- Provider 分布：bailian (63), openrouter (2), anthropic (6)\n\n**数据采集时间**: Wed 2026-03-11 00:30 GMT+8  \n**服务状态**: ✅ 运行中  \n**测试状态**: ✅ 所有子 agent 完成\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773160406320}}
